# Storage Redundancy 
- LRS
- ZRS
- GRS
- RA-GRS
- GZRS

## LRS (Locally Redundant Storage)
* 3 copies.
* Single datacenter.
* Lowest cost.
* Protects against hardware failure.
* Most common.

## ZRS (Zone Redundant Storage)
* Copies across Availability Zones.
* Protects against zone failure.
* Higher availability.
* Recommended for production.

## GRS (Geo Redundant Storage)
* Replicates to secondary region.
* Disaster recovery protection.
* Data available in paired region.

## RA-GRS
* Same as GRS.
* Secondary region can be read.

Useful for:
* Reporting
* Read-only workloads

## GZRS
* Zone redundancy + geo redundancy.
* Highest resiliency.
* Production critical applications.

# Storage Performance Tiers
## Standard HDD
* Lowest cost.
* Lowest performance.
* Archive workloads.

Use Cases:
* Backups
* Archive data

***

## Standard SSD
* Better performance.
* Moderate cost.
* General workloads.

Use Cases:
* Test environments
* Small production workloads

***
## Premium SSD
* High IOPS.
* Low latency.
* Production applications.

Use Cases:
* Databases
* Enterprise applications

***

## Premium SSD v2
* Better performance than Premium SSD.
* Flexible performance tuning.
* High throughput.

***

## Ultra Disk
* Highest IOPS.
* Lowest latency.
* Mission critical workloads.

Use Cases:
* SQL Server
* SAP HANA
* Large databases

***

# Access Tiers (Blob Storage)
- Hot Tier
- Cool Tier
- Archive Tier

## Hot Tier
* Frequently accessed data.
* Highest storage cost.
* Lowest access cost.

## Cool Tier
* Infrequently accessed data.
* Lower storage cost.
* Higher retrieval cost.

## Archive Tier
* Rarely accessed data.
* Lowest storage cost.
* Highest retrieval latency.

***

# Storage Security

## Storage Account Keys
* Full account access.
* Two keys provided.
* Can rotate keys.

## Shared Access Signature (SAS)

* Temporary access.
* Time limited.
* Permission limited.


## Private Endpoint
* Private IP access.
* No public internet exposure.
* Most secure approach.

## Service Endpoint

* Secure VNet access.
* Public endpoint still exists.
* Traffic remains on Azure backbone.

